ANSWER: Vaping (e-cigarettes) is prohibited in your dorm room. According to OP 91.301, "Tobacco use in any form, including e-cigarettes, shall not be permitted in any university facility or in vehicles owned or leased by the university, regardless of location." Since a dorm room is a university facility, this prohibition applies there. Additionally, OP 91.301 states that "Mississippi State University is a Smoke-Free Campus" and that the policy "applies to all students, faculty, staff, and visitors."

If you repeatedly violate this policy, you can be referred to the Dean of Students office, as noted in OP 91.301.

